Napoli and Super Eagles striker Victor Osimhen has tipped lovers on how to avoid being served ‘breakfast’ (heartbreak). The forward, who’s very active on his social media pages, particularly Twitter, dishing out quotes which many find inspirational and amusing, argued a drama-filled relationship will always head for the rocks. He said regardless of how much one is loved by their partner, they will exit the relationship if the individual is too problematic. “Always Remember That The Right Person Will Leave You If Your Wahala Is Too Much,” he tweeted. Reacting, many tweeps affirmed Osimhen’s assertion but a few insisted the right person would manage their lovers ‘wahala’ despite its magnitude. @zubbyifeaka tweeted: “So true, nobody wants extra stress.” @jayythedope said: “She’s replaceable and that’s fact.”   How to play social media game, by Blessing CEO     ‘Buga’ is a mega hit, says Davido     Ladipoe reveals reason behind name change from Poe   @FlexzyDan wrote: “Me trying to be calm so that I won’t loose the right person vs me 5 minutes later because i no send anybody papa.” @DimejiEgbeyemi stated: “The right person will never get tired of you, let that sink.” @egbalick tweeted: “Men spend their time frustrating some1 that truly love Dem, all in d name of am testing her. Good moral values does not hide. D only reason she stayed after been treated like sheet is d aforementioned qualities. If reverse to be d case will u tolerate those things. We are humans.” @Juliue_Owalu said: “Na before now them ready to face wahala for Benz than to face peace for Keke or bike.” @essyenpaul829 wrote: “The right person should know how to manage your wahala na @obi_dm stated: “We go manage the left person boss.”